1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE
RESOLUTION 1044 By: Crosswhite Hader, Stark,
4 and Stinson
5
6
7
8 AS INTRODUCED
9 A Resolution raising awareness for organ donation;
recognizing the month of April 2026 as National
10 Donate Life Month.
11
12
13 WHEREAS, one of the most meaningful gifts that a human being can
14 bestow upon another is the gift of life. In the last 30 years,
15 Donate Life America and the Donate Life Community have registered
16 170 million organ, eye, and tissue donors in the United States; and
17 WHEREAS, over 100,000 men, women, and children are currently on
18 the national waiting list for organ transplantation; and
19 WHEREAS, every 8 minutes another person is added to the waiting
20 list; and
21 WHEREAS, 13 people die each day because the organs they need are
22 not donated in time; and
23 WHEREAS, more than 49,000 organ transplants from 23,788 donors
24 brought new life to patients and their families in 2025; and
Req. No. 17240 Page 1

1 WHEREAS, more than 2,200 children under the age of 18 are on the
2 national transplant waiting list; and
3 WHEREAS, more than 1,874 children were saved by the generosity
4 of donors and donor families in 2025; and
5 WHEREAS, LifeShare of Oklahoma, the nonprofit organ procurement
6 organization, which is dedicated to the recovery of organs and
7 tissue for transplantation therapy in Oklahoma, with a mission to
8 honor donors and save lives through organ and tissue donation; and
9 WHEREAS, in 2003, the first National Donate Life Month campaign
10 was launched. National Donate Life Month takes place in April and
11 features an entire month of activities to encourage Americans to
12 register as organ, eye, and tissue donors and to honor those who
13 have saved lives through the gift of donation.
14 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
15 OF THE 2ND SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
16 THAT the Oklahoma House of Representatives supports the
17 recognition of the month of April 2026 as National Donate Life Month
18 and encourages all residents to consider giving life through organ
19 donation and to register with Oklahoma’s organ and tissue donor
20 registry by visiting www.lifeshareoklahoma.org or when renewing
21 their driver license.
